<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="225" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1149,2011]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1149,1174]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Postocellar seta absent. Palpus dark brown. Fore tibia black. Arms of genital fork convergent on distal 
<number box="[151,161,1186,1210]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[172,188,1186,1210]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
, widest point across arms only slightly wider than 
<number box="[767,800,1185,1210]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X width of base at midpoint; basal tubercles finger-like, contiguous. Distiphallus inflated apically, glans present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="227" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1149,2011]" box="[199,916,1257,1282]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,419,1257,1282]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body length 11.0 mm, wing length 8.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1149,2011]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Head mostly subshiny blackish-brown with very thin gray pollinosity. Frontal vitta brown with apex yellow, densely microsetulose, about 
<number box="[487,501,1330,1354]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[510,522,1330,1354]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="3.0">3</number>
width of frons; lower orbital plate dull pollinose; ocellar triangle black; median occipital sclerite with a small dark yellow spot at middle; lunule yellow; face pale yellow, densely microsetulose; gena dark yellow, lightly pollinose; clypeus uniformly blackish, shiny. Setae and setulae on head black; postocellar seta absent (
<figureCitation box="[293,376,1437,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Cothornobata atra sp. nov., male. A, left lateral; B, head; C, wing; D, genital fork; E, genitalia, left lateral; F, genitalia, posterior; G, aedeagus and associated structures, left lateral; H, aedeagus and associated structures, ventral; I, back of head, showing inner and outer vertical setae (Red spots mark the setal bases). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243810/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[347,376,1438,1462]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="13.0">
<date box="[347,376,1438,1462]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2013-01">13</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I); postgena with 
<number box="[578,592,1438,1462]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
strong seta at lower margin. Antenna brownish-yellow; first flagellomere 
<number box="[151,185,1473,1498]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.6">1.6</number>
X as long as broad; pedicel with 
<number box="[557,571,1474,1498]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
ventral apical seta nearly half length of first flagellomere; arista nearly 
<number box="[1381,1416,1473,1498]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="3.6">3.6</number>
X length of first flagellomere, brown, and long pubescent with distal half bare. Proboscis brownish-yellow with brown apex, setulae brown. Palpus dark brown, setulae black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1149,2011]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Thorax black, with pale gray pollinosity. Scutellum slightly convex, angled dorsally. Setae on thorax black, setulae blackish; katepisternum with 
<number box="[566,580,1618,1642]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="4.0">4</number>
strong setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1149,2011]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Legs mostly yellow, [mid leg broken]; coxae brown; apical 
<number box="[886,900,1653,1678]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[909,922,1653,1678]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="5.0">5</number>
of fore femur and apical 
<number box="[1219,1231,1654,1678]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1240,1269,1654,1678]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="20.0">20</number>
of hind femur black; fore tibia black, hind tibia dark yellow to brown, darker at base and apex; fore and hind tarsus brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1149,2011]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Wing brown with distal and discal bands dark brown; distal band basal to middle of distal section of M 
<number box="[1348,1356,1740,1754]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
; discal band along M 
<number box="[315,323,1779,1793]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
but posterior to R 
<number box="[544,552,1779,1793]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[561,568,1779,1793]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="5.0">5</number>
, basal to middle of penultimate section of M 
<number box="[1107,1115,1779,1793]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
. Bm-cu in line with CuA 
<number box="[1421,1429,1779,1793]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
, A 
<number box="[171,179,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
+CuA 
<number box="[247,255,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[264,299,1804,1828]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.2">2.2</number>
X as long as CuA 
<number box="[505,513,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
; distance between apex of R 
<number box="[846,854,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[863,870,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="3.0">3</number>
and R 
<number box="[947,955,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[964,971,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="5.0">5</number>
<number box="[980,1015,1803,1828]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="0.6">0.6</number>
X as long as M 
<number box="[1193,1201,1818,1832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
beyond dm-cu (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Cothornobata atra sp. nov., male. A, left lateral; B, head; C, wing; D, genital fork; E, genitalia, left lateral; F, genitalia, posterior; G, aedeagus and associated structures, left lateral; H, aedeagus and associated structures, ventral; I, back of head, showing inner and outer vertical setae (Red spots mark the setal bases). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243810/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1842,1866]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Halter pale yellow with brown base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1149,2011]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1436,1918,2032]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="226" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Abdomen mostly blackish with pale gray pollinosity, tergites 
<number box="[931,973,1878,1903]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
pale yellow with pale gray pollinosity apically. Pleuron dark gray. Epandrium dark brown. Genital fork dark brown, with blackish-brown to black setulae; arms strongly divergent basally and convergent on distal 
<number box="[814,824,1951,1975]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[835,851,1951,1975]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
, widest point across arms only slightly wider than 
<number box="[151,185,1986,2011]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X width of base at midpoint; basal tubercles finger-like, contiguous; medial tubercle strong, broadly convex Abbreviations: i vt s, inner vertical seta; o vt s, outer vertical seta.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243810/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" targetBox="[152,1431,211,1917]" targetPageId="25">
